      "beat_id": "B13",
      "t_start": 108,
      "estimated_duration_s": 21,
      "narration_text": "Two non-interacting particles in a 1D box, each in a different orbital. Distinguishable: ⟨(x₁−x₂)²⟩ = baseline. Fermions: baseline + exchange integral > baseline. Bosons: baseline − exchange integral < baseline. No Hamiltonian change — only the symmetry postulate.",
